      "back": "During a **network partition**, a distributed system must choose: refuse some requests (**consistency**) or serve possibly-stale data (**availability**). That's it \u2014 the choice only exists *during partitions*.\n\nCommon misstatements to avoid:\n- \"Pick 2 of 3\" \u2014 wrong; partitions aren't optional, so the real choice is C vs A *when* one happens.\n- Treating it as a system-wide permanent label \u2014 real systems choose **per operation** (reads may tolerate staleness; writes may require quorum).",
