      "back": "1. **Linearizable**: every operation appears to happen atomically at one point in real time; a read after a completed write *must* see it. Costs quorum coordination.\n2. **Causal**: operations that are causally related (reply after post) are seen in order by everyone; concurrent ops may be seen differently.\n3. **Read-your-writes**: a *session* guarantee \u2014 you always see your own writes; others may lag.\n4. **Eventual**: replicas converge if writes stop; no ordering promise in the meantime.",
