      "explanation": "Two honest caveats that mark an L5+ answer. First, W+R>N gives overlap, **not linearizability** \u2014 without read-repair discipline or a coordinator, \"sloppy\" quorums and concurrent writes can still serve stale/conflicting data (Dynamo-style systems pair this with vector clocks/LWW). Second, latency: quorum operations complete at the **median-slowest quorum member**, which is why W=3 of 5 across regions puts a cross-country RTT in every write.",
