      "explanation": "Entity diagrams describe what data means; access patterns describe how the system must retrieve and mutate it. Relational systems let you add indexes and joins as needs evolve, at a write and storage cost. Key-value and wide-column systems often require more decisions up front and denormalized views maintained by the write path.\n\nThe design review question is not \u201cWhich database scales?\u201d It is \u201cWhich expensive operation have we chosen, and is that cost bounded at expected scale?\u201d",
