      "front": "After a user updates their profile, the next page load reads an older value from a replica. The team wants to route every read to the primary. What should you do instead?",
      "back": "Start from the consistency contract for each read:\n\n1. Measure replication lag and identify the flows that cannot tolerate it.\n2. Give the writer **read-your-writes** behavior: temporarily route that user to the leader, carry a commit position and wait for a replica to catch up, or return the accepted value from client state.\n3. Keep lag-tolerant traffic\u2014public profiles, search, analytics\u2014on replicas.\n4. Define fallback behavior when replicas are stale or unavailable; do not allow an automatic fallback to overload the leader.\n\nRouting all reads to the primary removes read scale and can turn replica trouble into a primary outage.",
